9. Potential Pitfalls & Improvements in Your Current Code
  Neutral articles are currently skipped. Consider including them with a score of 0 (or using the neutral label's score if available).
  
  The "most relevant" article currently uses the title sentiment (not the summary) and picks the one with largest difference from the average. This may not be the most relevant. A better metric: highest absolute sentiment (most positive or most negative) or highest score confidence.
  
  Keyword filtering – you filter by keyword in summary, but the RSS feed may already be specific to the ticker. Perhaps you want to keep all articles for that ticker without keyword filtering? The current code could miss articles that don't contain the keyword but are relevant.
  
  Rate limiting – Yahoo Finance RSS might block frequent requests; add a delay between runs.
  
  Performance – calling the transformer model for each article is fine for a few articles, but for many articles, consider batching.

